checkers.nullness

Class RawnessSubchecker

  • java.lang.Object
    • javax.annotation.processing.AbstractProcessor

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Processor

    @TypeQualifiers(value={Raw.class,NonRaw.class,PolyRaw.class})
public class RawnessSubchecker
extends BaseTypeChecker
    A typechecker that is part of the Nullness type system. The Rawness Subchecker checks whether an object has been fully initialized by the constructor. If not, then some fields (that are annotated as @NonNull may still be null.
    See Also:
    NonNull, Nullable, Raw
    See the Checker Framework Manual:
    Nullness Checker
